  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dad\u0dd4\u0db8\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A Letter from the Cardinal to the Councillors",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Malcolm Cardinal Ranjith, the Archbishop of Colombo, in a letter addressed to all members of Parliament, has asked them to act in accordance with their conscience to choose a leadership that can realize the expectations of the motherland and the people, leaving aside corrupt activities such as party political power projects and buying MPs.",
        "The Cardinals also mentioned that the members are requested not to miss the historic opportunity to give the maximum contribution to the fulfillment of the people's aspirations.",
        "On a rare occasion when a president with all executive powers had to relinquish power, the extremely crucial decision to be taken for the future of the motherland is made according to their expectations. More than two million people of the country are watching the Parliament of Sri Lanka at this time. The Archbishop of Colombo has mentioned in his letter that there is a fear.",
        "The archbishop stated that it is a problem whether there is greed for power when looking at the experience and scandal faced by the former president who had to leave the power and the country even though he was in the hands of the executive power."
      ],
